    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-278586">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-278586">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,278586)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-278586">
																		Re:
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drclef" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(213153); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=213153&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610152340" alt="DrClef" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=213153)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drclef" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(213153); return false;" >DrClef</a></span> <span class="odate time_1223477011 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">08 Oct 2008 14:43</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-278586">
									

<p>Well, you're entitled to your opinion, of course. I just wrote what scares me personally.</p>
<p>I am, however, a bit confused as to why you think SCP-001 should implicate SCP-173 at all. 173 was the first one, yes, and a classic, but, well, its number is 173. It's one of many, which is what makes it so spooky: the idea that it's nothing special for the people who work with it, just another day at the job dealing with a malevolent and animate statue that strangles people unless it's watched constantly.</p>
<p>I still think that there should be no SCP-001, honestly. I wouldn't mind this being renumbered as, say, 999 or something, but this is my idea for the sort of huge thing that should be 001: Big enough to not only found the SCP Foundation, but also to turn on its head everything we know about how the Foundation operates. Entire emergency procedures should be dedicated to it. It should be huge enough not only to end existence, but also to have the feeling that there's nothing containing about the special containment procedures around it: we're just treading water and waiting for the end. That sorta thing.</p>
<p>Just my thoughts.</p>

							</div>

								
					
