					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-283427">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drclef" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(213153); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=213153&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610152340" alt="DrClef" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=213153)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drclef" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(213153); return false;" >DrClef</a></span> <span class="odate time_1224002355 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">14 Oct 2008 16:39</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-283427">
									

<p>I just wanted to make a quick statement.</p>
<p>There have been a lot of people who have made comments about how they want this proposal to be the Real SCP-001. Although flattering, I'm not sure that's a good idea.</p>
<p>First, I don't like the idea that all other proposals are just cover stories. I would much rather all other proposals include just as elaborate an othering as mine did. If it's things like memetic kill agents and lines about "false scp-001s," … well, is there really anything to indicate that my entry is nothing more than a huge cover-up by the Foundation to throw their enemies off track? Protect a completely fabricated file under heavy levels of sescrutity to send Chaos Insurgency on a wild-goose chase in the Middle East while the real SCP-001 sits safely in [REDACTED]?</p>
<p>Secondly, a large part of what makes the SCP series scary is the unknown. There are so many creepy things implied around the edges of the best-written SCPs (Tree-Like Horns, one of my favorites, has one of the best final lines in an SCP evar, I think.) If there is a set SCP-001, then a lot of the unknown gets taken out. That's part of the reason why I changed the ending of my proposal: someone else pointed out that it's scarier if everything still exists right now, and doom about to come is scarier than doom in progress.</p>
<p>Thirdly, what if someone else comes up with a much better concept for 001 than I did? That's part of the reason why I like haveing a fluid SCP-001: that way, if someone comes by with something even better than the current winner, we don't need to say, "so sorry, too late."</p>
<p>I guess all I'm REALLY saying in the end is that everyone should be entitled to their own opinion about what the Real SCP-001 is, and making any one of them the Real Deal Officially kinda takes the fun out of it.</p>

							</div>

								
					
